cs.LG, cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM

The paper is primarily focused on Federated Learning (FL) and its implementation over wireless Device-to-Device (D2D) networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the primary focus of the paper. The paper also deals with wireless communication protocols, which suggests that it could belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) or cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper proposes wireless protocols that implement DSGD, which is a distributed optimization algorithm, indicating that it could belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) as well. Finally, the paper also discusses over-the-air computing via sparsity-based recovery, which suggests that it could belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
